Sentencas: Single-chamber solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with an anode-supported Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte were operated in a mixture of butane and air at furnace temperatures of 200-300 degrees C.
Titulo: Single-chamber SOFCs with a Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte film for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: The electromotive force (emf) of the cell and the voltage drop were strongly influenced by the catalytic activity of the anode for the partial oxidation of butane.
Titulo: Single-chamber SOFCs with a Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte film for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: The promotion of hydrogen formation by the addition of Ru to the anode caused an increase in the emf and a reduction in the voltage drop.
Titulo: Single-chamber SOFCs with a Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte film for low-temperature operation

Sentencas: As a result, stable power densities of 44 and 176 mW cm(-2) were obtained at 200 and 300 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Single-chamber SOFCs with a Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 electrolyte film for low-temperature operation
